<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa Strikes Arms Deal With Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- South African arms
manufacturer Denel signed a 146-million-rand (24 million U.S.
dollar) contract with Britain, South African state television, the
SABC, reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, signed by Denel's Somchem and the British
Defense Ministry Friday night, was part of a one-billion-rand
(167million U.S. dollar) arms contract.
</P>
<P>
Somchem would develop artillery charges for Britain's AS-90
self- propelled guns, said the SABC.
</P>
<P>
The deal is the biggest in Somchem's 27-year history, it said.
</P>
<P>
Friday night's agreement was signed after four years of
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The deal would provide a considerable number of jobs for the
Western Cape-based Somchem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
