<HEADLINE> Arab League Chief Condemns Israeli Raids on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary-General Esmat
Abdel-Meguid on Saturday condemned the recent Israeli attack on
Lebanese civilian targets.
</P>
<P>
Arab countries "denounce Israel's fresh aggression against"
Lebanon and the Lebanese people, Abdel-Meguid said before leaving
here for Damascus, Syria for a meeting of the Arab Parliamentary
Union.
</P>
<P>
He said that he has telephoned Lebanese Prime Minister Salim
Hoss to voice condemnation of the Israeli assault.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation for rocket attacks on Israel's northern areas by
Lebanese guerrillas, Israel Thursday night launched air strikes
against civilians targets near Lebanon's capital of Beirut,
including power stations, bridges, roads and water plants, leaving
eight people dead and at least 60 others wounded.
</P>
<P>
During his visit in Damascus, Abdel-Meguid is expected to meet
with Syrian President Hafez al-Assad and Foreign Minister Farouq
al-Sharaa, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The talks will focus on a number of issues of interest to the
Arab nation, including the Middle East peace process and
restoration of Arab solidarity, the news agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
