<HEADLINE> Jordanian Parliament Condemns Israeli Air Raids on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Jordanian House of Deputies (
lower house of parliament ) Saturday denounced Israeli air raids
on Lebanese civilian targets as aggression against the Arab world
and Lebanon in particular.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the House condemned the Israeli attacks as "a
flagrant violation of international laws" which marked a "new
round of continuous assaults exercised haughtily by Israel against
our Arab world in general and Lebanon in particular."
</P>
<P>
It also affirmed support to the Lebanese people and called for
Arab countries to overcome their minor differences and take a
united stand to encounter Israel's expansion plans.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli attacks, carried out Thursday night on bridges and
power plants near Beirut, left eight civilians dead and over 60
others injured, reports said.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the Jordanian House called on Israel to
comply with United Nations Resolution 425 which called for Israeli
 troop withdrawal from southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
It also called on the United States, Russia and the European
Union to shoulder their responsibilities and subject Israel to
the international will.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein and Prime
Minister Abdel Raouf al-Rawabdeh also denounced the Israeli air
raids on Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah called for Israeli Prime Minister-elect Ehud Barak
to prevent what he called "Israeli extremists" from damaging
new hopes for the Middle East peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
