<HEADLINE> Russia Opposes Laying Pipeline on Caspian Sea Bed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Russian Deputy Foreign
Minister Yuri Proshin said here on Saturday that Russia opposes to
laying oil pipeline through the Caspian Sea bed due to
environmental issues and failure to finalize the Caspian Sea
legal regime.
</P>
<P>
Russia insists that Iran's route should be taken into
consideration for transferring the Caspian oil and gas, because of
its high importance from security and economical points of view,
Proshin told Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi.
</P>
<P>
He said that economic issues should be given due attention,
even though political issues are always taken into consideration.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Caspian Sea legal regime, the Russian
official said that the best solution to the issue is the division
of the sea, namely division of oil fields and of territorial
waters, free shipping and removal of any border among littoral
states.
</P>
<P>
The five Caspian Sea littoral states, Russia, Azerbaijan,
Iran, Turkmenistan and Kazakhstan hold different views on the
sea's legal regime.
</P>
<P>
Iran insisted on common ownership of the littoral states over
the sea while some others called for division of the sea among
littoral states.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi in the meeting said that Russia and Iran shoulder
a heavy responsibility in the political, economic and security
domains.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran and Russia are supposed to be able to play a
role in solving regional crises, which should not provide an
excuse for presence of foreign powers in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
