<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tunis Pledges to Combat Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNISIA, June 26 (Xinhua)-- The Tunisian government Saturday
pledged to work with the international community to combat drugs.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion of the International Anti-Drug Day which falls
on June 26, the Public Health Ministry said in a statement that it
is resolved to protect the country from drug smuggling and
narcotics addiction.
</P>
<P>
Tunis is contributing to the worldwide anti-drug efforts by
working with relevant international institutions, issuing laws and
joining the anti-drug U.N. and Arab League treaties, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The anti-drug policy adopted by Tunis and enforced by several
concerned agencies is based on prevention, vigilance and
strictness.
</P>
<P>
The statement called for continued vigilance against drugs in a
bid to spare the Tunisian society from the dangers of narcotics.
</P>
<P>
The Tunisian government has been attaching great attention to
drug combating and the security authorities have succeeded this
year in breaking up two drug taking and smuggling groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
