<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at  GMT, June 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Lebanese Prime Minister Salim Hoss said his
government will not be pressured into curbing the resistance
against Israeli occupation in the wake of the bloodiest Israeli
strike against the country since 1996.
</P>
<P>
"Resistance is a legal phenomenon in any country whose
territories are occupied. This is why Lebanon has the right to
resist the Israelis on its own land," Hoss told a news conference
at the premier palace Friday night. (BC-Lebanon-Israel-Resistance)
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Speaker of the Iraqi Parliament Saadoun Hammadi told
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan that over 1.11 million Iraqis
have died of shortage of medicines and more than 10 million others
are suffering from malnutrition as a result of U.N. santions on
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
In a letter intended to brief Annan on the consequences brought
about by the sanctions since 1990, Hammadi also said the embargo
has affected the environment as well as the educational, cultural
and all social aspects in Iraq, the Iraqi News Agency reported on
Saturday. (BC-Iraq-UN-Sanctions)
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Secretary-General of the Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) Jamil Al-Hujailan Saturday condemned the latest
Israeli air raids against Lebanese targets, saying it is proof of
Israel's hostile policy toward the Arabs.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli aggression on Lebanon took place at a time when
high hopes emerged for a pro-peace new Israeli government after
Labor Party leader Ehud Barak won the May elections, said the GCC
chief. (BC-GCC-Israel-Lebanon)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran Saturday afternoon set aflame 55 tons of various
narcotics seized from drug traffickers to mark the international
anti-drug day.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Deputy Secretary-General and Executive Director of the
U.N. International Drug Control Program Pino Arlacchi and senior
Iranian officials attended the ceremony on a hill in northern
Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Due to hot whether, the drug pile caught fire itself and
started burning some 20 minutes before the ceremony began.
(BC-Iran-Drug-Campaign)
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Arab League Secretary-General Esmat Abdel-Meguid on
Saturday condemned the recent Israeli attack on Lebanese civilian
targets.
</P>
<P>
Arab countries "denounce Israel's fresh aggression against"
Lebanon and the Lebanese people, Abdel-Meguid said before leaving
here for Damascus, Syria for a meeting of the Arab Parliamentary
Union. (BC-Arab League-Israel-Condemnation) 
</P>
