<HEADLINE> Two Charged in Dublin With Possessing Explosives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Two men from Northern Ireland were
charged in the Irish capital city of Dublin on Saturday with
possessing explosive material.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Ashe Mellon, 23, and Raymond Griffiths, 34, both from
Londonderry in Northern Ireland, were remanded in custody until
July 13, a Reuters report said.
</P>
<P>
They were arrested early on Thursday in the Irish border county
of Donegal after police stopped a suspect van and found it was
carrying bomb-making equipment near the border with Northern
Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The arrest came at a time of renewed tension in Northern
Ireland, as the implementation of a peace deal signed over a year
ago has stalled over the issue of when and how guerrilla weapons
should be destroyed.  
</P>
