<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Global Science Conference Opens in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Over 2,000 Scientists and
scientific policy makers from all over the world began to
investigate the apprehensions and opportunities of science in the
next century as World Conference on Science opened here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
By bringing together representatives of all stakeholers in
science, the conference, entitled "Science for the 21st Century",
was aimed at taking the debate of the achievements, shortcomings
and challenges of science and its social, economic and ethnic
implications in the years and decades to come, said a statement by
the U.N. Education, Science and Culture Organization (UNESCO) that
held the conference.
</P>
<P>
The passing century has witnessed amazing scientific
breakthroughs, and the applications of scientific knowledge has
become the most important engine for economic development, the
UNESCO said.
</P>
<P>
But the progress has come at a price with more frequent natural
disasters provoked by global warming, increasing scarcity of
drinking water, disappearing forests, plants and animal species
and air pollution reported around the world.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the general public is alarmed at both the
rate and the direction of science progress.
</P>
<P>
The after-effects of Chernobyl accident, the birth of Dolly the
cloned sheep and other transgenic animals, have raised the fears
of the consequence of scientists' fiddling dangerously with
Nature.
</P>
<P>
The World Conference on Science, the first global conference on
science since 1979, is welcomed by the scientific community.
</P>
<P>
"It is appropriate that the last major conference under UN
frame is on science," M.S. Swaminathan, the president of India's
M.S. Swaminathan Research Foundation, told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"Because the 20th century is a century of science," said
Swaminathan, a keynote speaker at the opening ceremony of the
conference, who is also UNESCO Chairman in Ecotechnology.
</P>
<P>
After Saturday's opening ceremony, the conference will be
divided into three forums. Twenty five topics about natural
science and its relationship with the human society will be
discussed during the next five days.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be concluded by adopting a Declaration on
Science and the Use of Scientific and a Science Agenda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
