<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Permits Air Passage of Russian Peacekeepers to Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Romania agreed Saturday to grant
the passage through its airspace to 10 Russian aircraft en route
to Kosovo transporting peacekeeping soldiers and military
equipment.
</P>
<P>
According to a communique by the Romanian Foreign Ministry and
Defense Ministry, the government granted the Russian request
raised Friday after urgent consultations with NATO.
</P>
<P>
Romania will treat Russia's request as an emergency case, which
means permission could take effect without approval from the
parliament, said the communique. Under Romanian laws, the passage
of foreign troops should be endorsed by the parliament except for
special and emergency cases, which can be permitted only by the
president.
</P>
<P>
In this circumstance, however, the foreign military aircraft
should pass through within four hours. Russia has agreed to
reformulate its half-hour flying interval to meet the regulation,
the communique said.
</P>
<P>
Romania on June 13 spiked Moscow's request for an air passage
to Kosovo because Russia had not reached an agreement with NATO on
the peacekeeping role in Kosovo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
