<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Global Science Conference Opens in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,000 scientists and
decision makers from all over the world are discussing the
challenges and opportunities of science in the next century as the
World Conference on Science opened here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
By bringing together representatives from all scientific fields,
the conference, entitled Science for the 21st century, will debate
the achievements, shortcomings and challenges of science as well
as its social, economic and ethnic implications in the decades to
come.
</P>
<P>
The passing century has witnessed amazing scientific
breakthroughs and the application of scientific achievements have
become a powerful engine for economic development.
</P>
<P>
But progress has come at a price of more natural disasters
provoked by global warming, an increasing scarcity of drinking
water, disappearing forests, plants and animal species, and air
pollution.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the after effects of the Chernobyl accident,
and the birth of Dolly the cloned sheep and other transgenic
animals have raised fears for scientists' dangerous game with
Nature.
</P>
<P>
The World Conference on Science, the first global conference on
science since 1979, was welcomed by the scientific community.
</P>
<P>
"It is appropriate that the last major conference in this
century under the auspices of the UN is on science," M.S.
Swaminathan, the president of India's M.S. Swaminathan Research
Foundation, told Xinhua. "Because the 20th century is a century of
science." Swaminathan, a keynote speaker at the opening ceremony
of the conference, is also a United Nations Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization Chair in Eco-technology.
</P>
<P>
After today's opening ceremony, the conference will be divided
into three forums and 25 topics will be debated during the next
five days.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be concluded by adopting a Declaration on
Science and a science agenda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
