<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC) Jamil Al-Hujailan Saturday condemned the
latest Israeli air raids against Lebanese targets, saying it is
proof of Israel's hostile policy toward the Arabs.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli aggression on Lebanon took place at a time when
high hopes emerged for a pro-peace new Israeli government after
Labor Party leader Ehud Barak won the May elections, said the GCC
chief.
</P>
<P>
Israeli warplanes, during the past two days, launched heavy
air raids against Lebanese infrastructure and civilian areas,
leaving at least eight people killed and 60 others wounded.
</P>
<P>
The GCC states support the general Arab stance calling for the
establishment of a just and comprehensive peace based on
respecting all related U.N. resolutions and the land-for-peace
principle, said Al-Hujailan.
</P>
<P>
He said the GCC countries have agreed that Israel must
implement all signed agreements with the Arabs, especially with
the Palestinian National Authority.
</P>
<P>
He called on the world community to double its efforts to build
a just and comprehensive peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
The GCC, a regional political and economic alliance
established in 1981, groups Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi
Arabia and the United Arab Emirates (UAE). 
</P>
