<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
Saturday announced 1.2 billion dollars in grants to hire 30,000
teachers for the new school year, a program approved by Congress
with bipartisan support last year.
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately there are some in Congress who are backing away
from their commitment to reduce class size" by financing a total
of 100,000 new teachers, Clinton said in his weekly radio address.
</P>
<P>
