the years when there are no elections," he said.
</P>
<P>
Clinton has turned to domestic issues after several months of
the Kosovo crisis as the 2000 presidential election is approaching.
</P>
<P>
Racing against the 2000 political calendar, Clinton promised
"to be working right up to the very end" of his term.
</P>
<P>
Clinton acknowledges the reality that "the closer you get to
the election the more difficult it will be to pass anything."
</P>
<P>
In a domestic policy speech Friday at Georgetown University,
Clinton called on Congress to approve his proposals on the issues
such as gun control, Medicare, Social Security and child care.
</P>
<P>
House Republicans, who are reluctant to cooperate with the
president, showcased their own priorities Friday to bolster
national security, improve education, cut taxes and safeguard the
Social Security surplus for improving the program.  
