<HEADLINE> Wanda Flops Again Chinese First Division </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- An injury time header and broiling
temperatures sank defending champions Dalian Wanda to another
defeat, a narrow 1-2 to Beijing Guo'an in a Chinese first division
soccer match here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wanda, who snatched their first win of the season on Thursday
with a 3-1 victory over Guangzhou Songri, found themselves back to
the familiar losing form as they fell to their 10th unwinning
match in the scorching Beijing sun.
</P>
<P>
Striker Nan Fang, boyfriend of the diving Olympic champion Fu
Mingxia, emerged as the hero of the home side, breaking the
deadlock in the 20th minute and killing the match for Guo'an with
a raking header in the 91st minute.
</P>
<P>
Wanda briefly revived their hopes for an away draw when center
forward Wang Tao levelled the match at 1-1 after 81 minutes, but
the four-time champions in the last five year failed to hold on.
</P>
<P>
The newly-appointed coach Li Yingfa, citing a sore throat, didn
't show up in the after-match news conference, while his
understudy, assistant manager Sui Wei blamed the hot weather for
their another dismal performance.
</P>
<P>
Wanda remained on the wrong end of the 14-team standings table
with nine points from 11 round of matches standing at the 13th
spot.
</P>
<P>
1995 league champions Shanghai Shenhua claimed the top spot for
the first time this season, after beating Guangzhou Songri 2-1 on
home turf.
</P>
<P>
Former pace-setters Sichuan Quanxing slided two places to the
third with their 1-2 away loss to Liaoning Fushun.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in today's action, Chongqing Longxin was forced to a
1-1 tie by visiting Shenzhen Ping'an; Luneng Taishan nipped
Shenyang Haishi for a 1-0 win; Jilin Aodong edged the bottom club
Wuhan Heart K 1-0 at home; Tianjin Taida scored a 1-0 narrow home
win over Qingdao Hainiu. 
</P>
