<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Speeding Up Community Service Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- China will try to speed up the
development of its service industry in urban communities, a senior
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
China's city dwellers usually live in close communities in
separate zones where services are in short supply. According to
one study of seven major Chinese cities, more than 70 percent of
the urban families badly need services like appliance repairs,
newspapers and house cleaning.
</P>
<P>
This area could absorb 11 million more workers, Yang Yanyin,
deputy minister of civil affairs, told Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that the community service business in China has been
developing rapidly since 1986, when the Civil Affairs Ministry
first called for growth in the sector. She said that it used to be
entirely government sponsored and most of those who benefited from
it were either handicapped or living in extreme poverty.
</P>
<P>
But these days urbanites can enjoy services available in their
neighborhoods so the next step is to socialize the community
service industry before industrializing the sector, she said,
explaining that in most major Chinese cities, funds from various
investors are being channeled into local service businesses.
</P>
<P>
At the preliminary stage, the most important purpose of
socialization of these services is still to maintain social
results and there is a long way to go before China can
industrialize the community service sector, she said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
