<HEADLINE> Frentzen Wins French GP in Rain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 27 (Xinhuia) -- Heinz-Harald Frentzen and his
Jordan team wiped off a rainy conditions at the French Grand Prix
on Sunday and took over a surprise victory in Magny-Cours of
France.
</P>
<P>
While his more illustrious rivals made two pit stops, the
German made only one to record the second GP win of his career.
</P>
<P>
Frentzen covered 72 laps of the 4.25-kilometer Magny-Cours
circuit ahead of Mika Hakkinen, who came from 14th position on the
starting grid to finish second and extend his lead of the world
drivers' championship.
</P>
<P>
Rubens Barrichello, who had pole position, came third, with
Ralf Schumacher in fourth. 
