<HEADLINE> Nepali Congress Wins 1 More Seat in Lower House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Nepali Congress now
holds 111 of the 205 seats in the House of Representatives after
winning in No. 3 constituency of Sunsari district which went to
the polls Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The general elections were held in May but due to the death of
candidates, elections in four constituencies were rescheduled for
June.
</P>
<P>
With the holding of the polls in Sunsari-3, all the 205 seats
in the house have been produced. But there are only 202 members in
the house as Nepali Congress President Girija Prasad Koirala,
General Secretary of the Communist Party of Nepal (Unified
Marxist-Leninist, CPN-UML) Madhav Kumar Nepal and CPN-UML central
committee member K.P. Sharma Oli were each elected from two
constituencies.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, by-elections have to be held in three
constituencies.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali Congress formed its majority government on May 31.
</P>
