<HEADLINE> NPC's Clarification on Right of Abode Issue Well Received in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of various
sectors in Hong Kong issued statements today to render their full
support for the interpretation of the relevant provisions of the
Basic Law concerning the right of abode issue by China's National
People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
They all hailed the move as a demonstration of safeguarding the
rule of law.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee issued its interpretation earlier
Saturday. The interpretation will drastically reduce the number of
mainlanders eligible for the right of abode to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong deputies to the NPC and members of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, expressed their all-out support for the NPC's
clarification, adding that the interpretation which clarifies the
legislative intent of the relevant provisions of the Basic Law is
lawful and reasonable.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the NPC's interpretation has been made after
widely soliciting opinions of different sectors in Hong Kong,
whose action is believed to win a wide support from the Hong Kong
residents because it conforms to their fundamental interest and to
safeguarding the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
In their statements, local industrialists and businessmen
agreed that the NPC's interpretation will help improve Hong Kong's
commercial environment and benefit its long-term stability and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Many lawyers pointed out that the NPC's interpretation will not
bring a bit of harms to the spirit of a high-degree of autonomy
and judicial independence for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Actually, it helps Hong Kong solve its practical problems and
maintain the normal order of its society.  
</P>
</TEXT>
