<HEADLINE> HK Newspapers Welcome NPC's Interpretation of Basic Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Major Hong Kong-based newspapers
voiced support today for the interpretation of the Basic Law by
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC),
saying that the move helps maintain Hong Kong's prosperity,
stability and the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-language newspaper "Wen Wei Po" said in an
editorial that the NPC Standing Committee's interpretation of the
Basic Law gives the most authoritative and accurate explanation of
the legislative intent of some provisions.
</P>
<P>
The courts of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
have then criteria to follow when citing some provisions of the
Basic Law in the trial.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that the NPC Standing Committee's
interpretation reflects the will of the general public, including
all circles of Hong Kong and foreign investors in the region.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors all regard the interpretation as beneficial
to the Hong Kong residents and business circle, and it will by no
means weaken the judicial independence of Hong Kong, the newspaper
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The "Ta Kung Pao" newspaper noted that interpretation adopted
by the NPC Standing Committee is of extremely significance to
increase the Hong Kong residents' understanding of the Basic Law
and rule of the region by law.
</P>
<P>
Facts show that social disorder may arise if people do not act
in accordance with the Basic Law, it said, noting that only with a
true observation of the Basic Law can the SAR's power of final
adjudication and the status of judicial independence be ensured.
</P>
<P>
The interpretation gives a more clear definition on the
qualifications of those inland children born of the Hong Kong
residents, it said, and makes sure that they would come to Hong
Kong in order and jointly contribute to Hong Kong's development.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper also praised the correct, wise and lawful
measures taken by the chief executive and the SAR government in
solving the right of abode issue.
</P>
<P>
The SAR government managed to prevent some social problem that
may occur with the possible influx of 1.67 million immigrants and
soundly settled the issue with the help of the central government.
</P>
<P>
In an editorial, the Hong Kong commercial daily noted that the
rule of law is the basis for social stability, and to safeguard
the rule of law requires the concerted efforts of all the citizens
in the SAR.
</P>
<P>
The NPC's interpretation does not mean interfering into the
judicial independence of the SAR and will not harm the
authoritativeness of the Court of Final Appeal, it noted.
</P>
<P>
The SAR government, the central government, and the NPC all
respect the SAR's judicial independence and safeguard the
authoritativeness of the Court of Final Appeal, the newspaper said.
</P>
</TEXT>
