<HEADLINE> Chinese Academy of Science Sets New Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS) has new scientific and technological development goals for
the next few years, with agricultural technology high on the list.
</P>
<P>
Other important fields include population and health,
information technology, energy, new materials, advanced
manufacturing techniques, resources and the environment, and space
technology.
</P>
<P>
CAS has changed its focus and established some new projects
that help promote scientific and economic development in the 21st
century. The new areas include agricultural technology, life
science, and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
CAS is also planning scientific projects with major social and
economic results in a short period of time and some medium and
long-range projects that are hoped to make a breakthrough in
various fields.
</P>
<P>
Some projects that are vital to state security and the
sustained development of Chinese society will also be implemented
over the next few years. 
