<HEADLINE> Chinese Professor Given French Honor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Professor Wu Liangyong of Qinghua
University, who is a member of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and
Chinese Academy of Engineering, was given France's culture and
arts medal recently.
</P>
<P>
French Ambassador to China Pierre Morel presented Wu with the
medal for his outstanding contributions to Sino-French exchanges
in architecture.
</P>
<P>
The honor was established by the French Ministry of Culture for
people from different countries who have outstanding achievements
in culture, the arts, and international cultural exchanges. Wu is
the first Chinese citizen to win the award.
</P>
<P>
The 77-year-old Wu was in charge of design work on many major
projects in China and has a reputation in construction design,
urban planning, and education and has won several major
international prizes.
</P>
<P>
With his help, Chinese and French departments held an
exhibition of contemporary French architecture in Beijing and an
exhibition of traditional and contemporary Chinese architecture in
Paris. 
</P>
