<HEADLINE> Kenya Choose Provisional Squad for Athletics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Three world champions features in
the Kenyan squad announced here today for the forthcoming
athletics world championships.
</P>
<P>
Men's 5000 meters champion Daniel Komen, men's 3000 meters
steeplechase winner Wilson Boit and women's 10,000 meters gold
medalist Sally Barsosio at the 1997 world championships in Athens
will lead the Kenyan team for Seville next month.
</P>
<P>
Among the Kenyan provisional 100-strong squad also are Tegla
Lorupe, twice New York marathon women's champion and holder of the
world's best time for the women's marathon, Paul Tergat, five-
times world cross-country champion, Benjamin Limo, world cross-
country short-course title-holder and 3,000 meters steeplechase
world record-holder Bernard Barmasai.
</P>
<P>
Kenya's athletics chiefs decided against naming definitive
teams when the national championships ended at the weekend in
Nairobi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
