<HEADLINE> Sixteen People Injured in Blast in Eastern Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Berlin, June 27 (Xinhua) -- About 16 people were injured
earlier on Sunday when an explosion occurred in an entertainment
complex in the eastern German state of Saxony-Anhalt.
</P>
<P>
The explosion went off at 1:30 a.m. local time (11:30 GMT
Saturday) outside a bar that was part of the entertainment complex.
</P>
<P>
Two of the five most seriously injured were taken to a hospital
by helicopter, a police spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said, "It's not an accident, and something was deposited
here."
</P>
<P>
The cause of the blast was not immediately known. 
</P>
