<HEADLINE> Ayala Takes WBA Bantamweight Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Paulie Ayala took the World
Boxing Association bantamweight title by outpointing Johnny Tapia
on unanimous decision in Las Vegas, the United States on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Judge Guy Jutras of Canada scored it 115-114 and Fernando Viso
of Venezuela and Duane Ford of Las Vegas each scored it 116-113
for the new 118-pound champion.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Tapia now dropped to 46-1-2 with 25 knockouts
while left-hander Ayala improved to 28-1 with 12 knockouts.
</P>
