<HEADLINE> Jacobs Posts Best Time of Year for Women's 1,500 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- World silver medalist Regina
Jacobs of the United States posted the best time of the year for
women's 1,500 meters at the U.S. athletics championships in Eugene,
Oregon, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Jacobs clocked four minutes 2.41 seconds to win the race,
followed by runner-up Stephanie Best at 4:08.53. Shayne Culpepper
was third at 4:08.69.
</P>
<P>
The top three finishers in the championships qualify for August
's world championships in Seville, Spain if the their results have
met the qualifying standard.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 400 meters, Jerome Young beat his former coach,
Antonio Pettigrew, to win in the second-fastest time of the year,
44.24 seconds. Pettigrew clocked 44.59 while third-placer Jerome
Davis clocked 44.91. 
</P>
</TEXT>
