<HEADLINE> 16 Britons Detained for Illegal Working in Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Sixteen British nationals were put
in custody Saturday following a massive police swoop of bars and
discos in Cyprus' southeast Ayia Napa town, the local Sunday Mail
newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the 16, aged mainly between 18-23, are suspected of
working illegally and harassing tourists by aggressively touting
for business in Ayia Napa's main square where the pubs and clubs
are situated.
</P>
<P>
Scores of Cypriot police took part in the raids on the bustling
holiday resort which entertains up to a million tourists a year.
</P>
<P>
Scores of officers from the drug squad, immigration police and
the elite mobile rapid response unit were involved in the swoop.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus government is highly sensitive about the issue of
illegal foreign workers after recent reports that illegal
immigrants are entering the island every day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
