<HEADLINE> Fierce Fighting Kills, Wounds 100 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A fierce fighting that erupted
Saturday between Sri Lankan government troops and Tamil rebels in
the north of the country has killed and wounded at least 100
people, the Defense Ministry announced Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A military spokesman said 16 government force personnel were
killed during an operation aiming to expand the control area in
the northwest Wanni in northern Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Government forces brought under their control 61 square
kilometers of land area during the operation.
</P>
<P>
Another 33 soldiers were wounded during this operation which
continued from Friday morning till late afternoon, said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
During the operation, 41 rebels of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) have been confirmed killed, said the spokesman,
adding that a large number of rebels confirmed to have been
wounded.
</P>
<P>
In recent months, government troops have intensified their
offensive to capture more land in a bid to dry up LTTE's
resources.
</P>
<P>
LTTE rebels have been fighting a 16-year secessionist war
against the Sri Lankan government for a Tamil homeland in the
north and east of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
