<HEADLINE> 10th Special Olympics World Summer Games Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RALEIGH, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The 10th Special Olympics World
Summer Games opened Saturday night in Raleigh, capital of North
Carolina State of the United States, in a festive ceremony with
the participation of 7,000 athletes and 2,000 coaches from 152
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The "Flame of Hope" for the games was lit in Carter-Finley
Stadium of North Carolina State University, where some 50,000
spectators gathered for the opening ceremony featuring dances and
music.
</P>
<P>
During the nine-day games, the athletes with mental retardation
will compete in 19 events including aquatics, athletics, badminton,
basketball bocce, bowling, cycling, equestrian, golf, gymnastics,
powerlifting roller skating, sailing, soccer, softball, table
tennis, team handball, tennis and volleyball.
</P>
<P>
The matches will be held at venues throughout Raleigh and its
nearby towns of Durham, Chapel Hill and Cary.
</P>
<P>
The 10th Special Olympics World Summer Games, sanctioned by the
Special Olympics International (SOI), is the world's largest
sports event of the year.
</P>
<P>
Since 1968 when it was established, the SOI has staged nine
summer Special Olympics Games and six winter versions.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, composed of 58 mentally disabled people, will
compete in such disciplines as soccer, basketball, athletics,
swimming, gymnastics and table tennis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
