<HEADLINE> Roundup: HK Anticipates Bigger Role in Int'l Sports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
by sportswriter Liang Jinxiong
</P>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region of China is determined to reinforce its
image as an international metropolis by playing a more active role
in the world sports arena.
</P>
<P>
This was reflected by Hong Kong's recent decision to bid for
the 2006 Asian Games for the first time in its history.
</P>
<P>
