<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Enter Quarterfinals of Women's World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, June 26 (Xinhua) -- World Cup new-comers Russia
entered the women's World Cup soccer tournament quarterfinals with a
4-1 victory over Canada on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian team started strongly in the first half, hoping to
get an early goal in the match which decided which team qualify for
the quarterfinals as the runners-up of the Group C.
</P>
<P>
The Australians took a slight upper hand in the first half, but
failed to score a goal.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team were obviously more experienced, they played
defensively in the first half, making preprations for their attack
in the second half.
</P>
<P>
The two teams played to a goalless draw after the first 45
minutes and in the second half, the Australian team seemed a little
bit tired while the Russia team took over the domination.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team had 5 shots in the first 10 minutes of the
second half. They efforts got rewarded as captain Irina Grigorieva
beat Canadian goal-keeper Nicci Wright at the 54th minute.
</P>
<P>
Some 12 minutes later, Grigorieva made an assist to enable her
teammate Elena Fomina score to put Russia 2-0 ahead.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian team played desperately after being 2-0 down.
Charmaine Hooper narrowed the margin to 2-1 at the 76th minute. But
they hopes of levelling the scoring were dashed by Fomina and Olga
Karasseva who scored at the 86th and 90th minutes respectively.
</P>
<P>
Grigorieva was happy to score the first goal for her team:"It
was an important goal. In the second half we were on the ball. I
was really happy to be the one to score."
</P>
<P>
Grigorieva said:"Our next goal is to fight the Chinese team. We
are fully award that the Chinese team are the favorites. We will
fight to the end."
</P>
<P>
"Sydney is looming, dominating all of our thoughts." said
Grigorieva said.
</P>
<P>
Grigorieva said she had no idea what tactics they would adopt
against the favored Chinese team:"I have no idea now, that is for
the coach to determine. Maybe a few days will pass and then we will
work on them."
</P>
<P>
The Russian team will play China in the quarterfinals at San Jose
on June 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
