<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Hold Special Festivals for New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The New Light of Myanmar newspaper
Sunday urged the country's tourist sector to make preparations for
the arrival of more tourists in Myanmar in the new year period of
2000.
</P>
<P>
The country's three special zones -- Bagan and Mandalay
cultural zones in Mandalay division and Inlay natural zone in Shan
state -- are recommended to hold special festivals for tourists as
these are the places, to which 20 to 50 percent of the foreign
tourists visiting Myanmar, used to go.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a major foreign-invested hotel in the capital of
Yangon has planned to make a program to hold fireworks display
from Christmas Day in 1999 to the New Year Day to mark the
ushering of the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The paper urged entrepreneurs engaged in tourism to grasp the
opportunities to develop the tourism industry and tourism-related
businesses in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, a total of 340,123 foreign
tourists visited Myanmar in 1998. Myanmar is trying to boost the
number of tourist arrivals to 500,000 in the fiscal year
1999-2000.
</P>
<P>
At the end of March of this year, there were 21
foreign-invested hotels and 439 local-run motels, hotels and inns
in the country, the statistics added.
</P>
<P>
Another official statistics show that as of the end of April
this year, foreign investment in 29 hotels and tourism projects in
Myanmar amounted to 1.1 billion U.S. dollars. 
