<HEADLINE> China, Cuba Sail into Final in Women's Volleyball Masters Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTREUX, Switzerland, June 26 (Xinhua) -- China beat Italy
while Cuba defeated Brazil in the semifinals here on Saturday to
enter the Women's Volleyball Masters Tournament final.
</P>
<P>
The Italians surprised the Olympic runners-up by surging to a 4-
0 lead in the opening set.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese rallied to level the score 10-all but consecutive
unforced errors in service, setting and spiking finally cost the
Asians the first set, losing 22-25.
</P>
<P>
China appeared to wake up in the second set, leading 10-0 at
the beginning and maintaining a comfortable margin of four to five
points throughout before winning 25-20.
</P>
<P>
In the third set, China trailed the Italians 6-0 but coach Hu
Jin made several replacements as the Asian champions clawed back
to level at 11-all.
</P>
<P>
After taking the third set 25-18, the Chinese possessed the
psychological advantage over the Italians in the fourth set and
wrapped their victory 25-17.
</P>
<P>
This set up Sunday's clash in the final with the Cubans, who
beat the Chinese to win the Atlanta Olympic gold medal in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Cuba advanced into the final by beating arch-rivals Brazil 25-
21, 22-25, 25-21, 25-21.
</P>
<P>
Brazil and Italy will vie for the third place while Russia and
Canada meet in the play-off for the fifth place on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Russia gained the right for the play-off by beating Japan 25-18,
23-25, 25-22, 25-21 while Canada was the surprise winner against
the United States with 27-25, 25-23, 25-21. 
</P>
