<HEADLINE> More Sri Lankan Teachers to Work in the Maldives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Education Ministry has
called for applications from the country's teachers who have
two-to- three years' experience at middle and secondary level
schools for teaching appointments in the Maldives in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The closing date for the applications is July 28 this year, and
teachers with a sound knowledge of English and below 55 years as
on January 1 next year will be eligible to apply, the ministry
sources were quoted as saying on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said within one month after the closing date,
authorities from both the education ministries of Sri Lanka and
the Maldives will interview the candidates.
</P>
<P>
At the present, the Maldives requires teachers for Physics,
Biology, Commerce, Mathematics, Art, Physical Education, Accounts,
History, Chemistry, Social Studies, Computing Studies and the
English Language.
</P>
<P>
Under a bilateral agreement, it has been the practice for
several years for Sri Lanka to send its teachers to the Maldives
to help upgrade the Maldives education system, the sources said.
</P>
