<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Reaffirms Support to Latin American Anti-Drug War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A European Union
representative reaffirmed here Saturday that the EU supports the
Latin American and Caribbean countries in their war against drugs.
</P>
<P>
EU vice commissioner Manuel Marin, a Spaniard who is here to
attend the June 28-29 summit of Latin America, the Caribbean and
the EU, said that the European bloc recognizes the principle of "
shared responsibility" in fighting drugs.
</P>
<P>
He said that Europe admitted its responsibility many years ago
that the drug consumers were responsible for drug flooding and
thus adopted specific measures to promote the exports from the
Andean Community, including a zero customs duty for the group's
industrial products.
</P>
<P>
The Andean Community groups Peru, Ecuador, Bolivia, Colombia
and Chile.
</P>
<P>
Marin criticized the United States, the biggest market for
drugs, for its annual unilateral "certification" policy of "
punishing or rewarding" drug-producing countries in light of their
anti-drug policies and actions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
