<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin:
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippines' bamboo industry could be the country's next
top export enterprise in the coming millennium and a major
contribution to the economic development.
</P>
<P>
Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology said
Saturday that Mayon volcano is still restive and the alert remains
at No.1, as explosion may still occur.
</P>
<P>
Malaya:
</P>
<P>
-- Formal peace talks between the Philippine government and the
Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) are expected to start next
month, a senior MILF official said Saturday. 
</P>
