<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Costa Rica to Close Six Embassies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica has decided to close
six embassies starting August 1 to cut expenses, the Foreign
Affairs Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Central American country will close its embassies in
Romania, Greece, South Korea and the Czech Republic as well as its
consulates in San Francisco, the United States, and Guayaquil,
Ecuador, said Buillermo Alvarado, a Foreign Ministry official.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the move will save the country 384,000 U.
S. dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Roberto Rojas said that the closure of
embassies and consulates is designed to enable the country to
concentrate its diplomatic efforts in the countries where it has
economic and commercial interests.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica closed its embassy in Portugal and seven consulates
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
