<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bolivian President Hails Latin America-EU Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Bolivian President Hugo
Banzer said Saturday that the Latin America-European Union Summit
will become a bridge to unite the two continents.
</P>
<P>
After arriving here to attend the summit scheduled for June 28-
29, the president said that Latin America and Europe must promote
their economic, service, commodity and personnel movement.
</P>
<P>
According to the preliminary agenda, Banzer will talk about the
war against drug trafficking, terrorism and organized crime on
behalf of Latin America before the 45 chiefs of state and of
government attending the summit.
</P>
<P>
Banzer will meet with the presidents of some Andean Community
member states.
</P>
<P>
Banzer was one of the first heads of state to arrive here for
the summit. Most of the others will arrive on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
